name: S tím bláznem si nic nezačínej
Boll Weevil
comments: Blues & Gospel Records, 1890-1943, Compiled by Robert M. W. Dixon, John Godrich and Howard Rye Vera Hall, vocals; unaccompanied, recorded in Livingston, Alabama for the Library of Congress, Matrix 1323-A-1 First recording: "Boll Weevil" on July 23, 1937 made by John Lomax in Livingston, Alabama (presented here). Second recording: "Boll Weevil Blues" on October 31, 1940 made by John Lomax and Ruby Pickens Tartt in Livingston, Alabama. Released on: Afro-American Blues and Game Songs . Third recording: "Boll Weevil Holler" during the summer of 1959 made by Alan Lomax in Livinstone, Alabama. Released on: Southern Folk Heritage Series Recorded in the Field by Alan Lomax
